Portfolio metrics and watershed characteristics

M. Snyder

Mar.17, 2021

All watersheds

Three populations have no HighCritHab_m. While HighCritHab_m had the highest correlation (0.62) with mean spawner abundance, it isnt a great measure of watershed size for the populations with 0 values. The second highest correlation was with TotalLength_m (0.54), which is also from the NMFS critical habitat layer. I drop variables indicating watershed size from analysis (-HighCritHab_m, -HighCritHab_p, -HighIP_m, -Watershed_sqkm, -HighIP_p). Use meters of critical habitat as the variable representing watershed size (TotalLength_m). See file:///L:/Priv/CORFiles/Projects/ACE_CIVA_2.8/Marcia/R_code/OCC_Abundance_Size_Metrics.html for details.

Since, TotalLength_m is representing watershed size, the other variables are in terms of percent of the watershed area or length rather than area or length.

Before doing the PCA, I scale the variables by subtracting the mean and dividing by the standard deviation rather than adding one and taking the log as Griffiths et al.2014 did because negative numbers cant be logged.

PCA interpretation

Based on eigen values values I use principal components 1-3 in the rest of the script. I think there is some support for PC3 which explains ~6-7% of the variance each but I think a 10% of variance explained is a more robust cut-off.

Variable loadings

  • The eigen vec function outputs the weights of the variables in the linear equations that define the principal components.
  • The structure coefficients are simple linear correlation coefficients between the original variables and the principal components. In contrast to the eigenvector coefficients, the structure coefficients are correlations and directly measure the strength of the linear relationship between each variable and each principal component.
  • Final communalities are the sum of the squared structure correlations and represent the percentage of a variables variance that is linearly account for by the retained principal components.
# eigen vectors
